High risk of stroke in ANCA-associated vasculitis-a population-based study.
The incidence rate of stroke in AAV is higher than in the general population. High platelet count at AAV diagnosis was associated with increased risk of stroke.
Pubmed   Journal   ReadQx 
Is the relationship between deprivation and outcomes in rheumatoid arthritis mediated by body mass index? A longitudinal cohort study.
People with RA living in deprived areas have a higher burden of disease, which is partly mediated through obesity. Weight-loss strategies in RA could be better targeted towards those living in deprived areas.
Pubmed   Journal   ReadQx 
Ocular manifestations of ANCA-associated vasculitis.
 Ocular manifestations occur in al forms of AAV, especially in GPA. Clinicians should be mindful of the wide spectrum of ocular disease in AAV, caused by active vasculitis, disease-associated damage, and toxicities of therapy.
Pubmed   Journal   ReadQx 
Prevalence and predictors of atlanto-axial subluxation in rheumatoid arthritis after 12-years' follow-up (ESPOIR Cohort).
 In conclusion, the prevalence of aAAS after 12years was 4.6% in the ESPOIR cohort, with no patients having severe aAAS. Although some factors were found statistically associated to AAS, the event is too rare to allow a clinical relevance.
